OL,3,CSteve Tandy: 'There's no magic wand or
OL,4,Cquick fix ` I believe in Welsh talent'
OL,6,FTandy becomes the first Welshman to
OL,7,Fcoach the national side since 2007, at
OL,8,Fa time when Wales have slipped to 12th
OL,9,Fin the world rankings and had lost 17
OL,10,Fsuccessive matches before beating
OL,11,FJapan last month in the final game of
OL,12,FMatt Sherratt's interim reign.
OL,14,F"The privilege and the honour to be
OL,15,Fhead coach of your national country is
OL,16,Fmassive," Tandy said.
OL,18,F"Being in the changing rooms is even
OL,19,Fbetter. I've got huge pride as a sense
OL,20,Fof family and what a great rugby
OL,21,Fnation it is.
